Feature: Successful flow
    We enqueue and merge PRs one by one; everything goes well.

    Scenario: Enqueue one PR
        Given PR '1' exists

        When Flow starts
        Then Markers exist:
            | PR | MARKER | EXIST |
            | 1  | head   | yes   |
            | 1  | rebase | no    |
            | 1  | merge  | no    |
            | 1  | bad    | no    |
            | 1  | source | no    |

        When PR '1' is enqueued
        Then Push was called '1' time
        #    , for queue
        But  Branch 'target' does not match branch 'queue'
        # TODO: more specifically, *target is behind queue
        # TODO: check commit messages
        And  Markers exist:
            | PR | MARKER | EXIST |
            | 1  | head   | yes   |
            | 1  | rebase | yes   |
            | 1  | merge  | yes   |
            | 1  | bad    | no    |
            | 1  | source | yes   |
        And  For PR '1', marker 'source' matches its original commit
        And  For PR '1', marker 'head' matches its original commit
        #   , because branch does not move if already on top
        And  For PR '1', marker 'rebase' matches branch 'target'
        And  For PR '1', marker 'merge' matches branch 'queue'

        When PR '1' is merged
        Then Push was called '2' times
        And  Branch 'target' matches branch 'queue'
        #    , for pr branch and for main
        And  Markers exist:
            | PR | MARKER | EXIST |
            | 1  | head   | no    |
            | 1  | rebase | no    |
            | 1  | merge  | no    |
            | 1  | bad    | no    |
            | 1  | source | no    |
